Django Capstone Project

********Description********

This project is a Django-based web application designed as a capstone project. It includes functionalities to demonstrate the core features of Django and containerization using Docker.


Getting Started
********Prerequisites********

Ensure you have the following installed:

  > Python 3.x
  > pip (Python package installer)
  > Docker (if using Docker setup)

********Setting Up with Virtual Environment********

1. Clone the Repository

2. Create and Activate a Virtual Environment

3. Install Requirements

4. Apply Migrations

5. Run the Development Server
   > Access the application at http://127.0.0.1:8000/.


********Setting Up with Docker********

1. Clone the Repository

  > git clone https://github.com/yourusername/django-capstone.git
  > cd django-capstone


2. Build the Docker Image

  > docker build -t django-capstone .

3. Run the Docker Container

  > docker run -p 8000:8000 django-capstone

  > Access the application at http://127.0.0.1:8000/.

********Configuration********

********Environment Variables********

This project requires environment variables for sensitive information. Create a .env file in the root directory with the following variables:

DJANGO_SECRET_KEY=your_secret_key
DATABASE_URL=your_database_url

Ensure you do not commit this .env file to version control. Add it to .gitignore to keep it private.

********Database Setup********

If using Docker, the database configuration should be handled in the Dockerfile or docker-compose.yml if provided.

********Documentation********

The documentation is available in the docs directory and was generated using Sphinx.

********Contributing********

Feel free to fork this repository and submit pull requests. For major changes, please open an issue first to discuss what you would like to change.